{"word":"ἄπληστος","slug":"ἄπληστος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄπληστος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πίμπλημι'><el>πίμπλημι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>not to be filled, insatiate</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>ἄπλ. χρημάτων</el> <i>insatiate of</i> money, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <el>ἀπλήστως ἔχειν</el> to be <i>insatiate</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <el>ἀπλ. διακεῖσθαι</el> or <el>ἔχειν πρός τι</el> <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}